 HD95 WT: 41.608 mm\nSubject BraTS2021_01026: Dice WT: 0.9775 | HD95 WT: 1.732 mm\nSubject BraTS2021_01356: Dice WT: 0.9243 | HD95 WT: 8.000 mm\n\n=== FINAL TEST RESULTS ===\n  mean_dice_all: 0.89994\n  mean_hd95_WT: 8.014\n  TC_Dice: 0.8951\n  WT_Dice: 0.9202\n  ET_Dice: 0.8845\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1400x900 with 6 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":14},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4B — Seg-Grad-CAM (Explainable AI)\nManual PyTorch hooks — no `medcam` required.\n\nGrad-CAM formula:\nα_k^c = (1/N) Σ_{i,j,d} ∂y^c/∂A^k_{i,j,d}   |   M^c = ReLU(Σ_k α_k^c · A^k)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ── 4B: Seg-Grad-CAM via manual PyTorch hooks ─────────────────────────────────\n# Hooks the deepest Swin Transformer block, back-propagates the mean class score,\n# weights feature channels by their gradient magnitude, reconstructs a 3D heatmap.\n# NO medcam dependency — medcam's inject() API was removed in recent versions.\n\nclass SegGradCAM:\n    CANDIDATES = [\"swinViT.layers4.0\",\"swinViT.layers3.0\",\n                  \"swinViT.layers2.0\",\"swinViT.layers1.0\"]\n\n    def __init__(self, model, layer_name):\n        self.model = model; self._act = None; self._grad = None; self._hooks = []\n        self.layer_name = layer_name\n        # resolve dotted path\n        m = model\n        for p in layer_name.split(\".\"):\n            m = m[int(p)] if p.isdigit() else getattr(m, p)\n        self._hooks.append(m.register_forward_hook(\n            lambda mod,inp,out: setattr(self,\"_act\",out.detach())))\n        self._hooks.append(m.register_full_backward_hook(\n            lambda mod,gi,go: setattr(self,\"_grad\",go[0].detach())))\n\n    def remove_hooks(self):\n        for h in self._hooks: h.remove(); self._hooks.clear()\n\n    def generate(self, inp, cls_idx, sp_size):\n        self.model.eval(); self._act = None; self._grad = None\n        self.model.zero_grad()\n        with torch.enable_grad():\n            x   = inp.clone().detach().requires_grad_(True)\n            out = self.model(x)\n            out[0, cls_idx].mean().backward()\n        if self._act is None:\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Hook did not fire for {self.layer_name}\")\n        # global average pooling of gradients → channel weights\n        w   = self._grad[0].mean(dim=0)                         # (C,)\n        cam = F.relu((self._act[0] * w.unsqueeze(0)).sum(-1))   # (L,)\n        # reshape token sequence to 3D grid\n        L = cam.shape[0]; g = round(L**(1/3))\n        cam3d = cam.reshape(g,g,g) if g**3==L else                 F.pad(cam,(0,(g+1)**3-L)).reshape(g+1,g+1,g+1)\n        cam_up = F.interpolate(cam3d.float()[None,None], size=sp_size,\n                               mode=\"trilinear\", align_corners=False).squeeze().cpu().numpy()\n        lo,hi = cam_up.min(), cam_up.max()\n        return ((cam_up-lo)/(hi-lo+1e-8)).astype(np.float32)\n\n    @classmethod\n    def attach(cls, model):\n        for name in cls.CANDIDATES:\n            try:\n                inst = cls(model, name)\n                logger.info(f\"SegGradCAM attached to: {name}\")\n                return inst\n            except AttributeError: continue\n        raise RuntimeError(\"No valid Swin layer found\")\n\n# ── Run on first test subject ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\nPath(f\"{CFG.output_dir}/gradcam\").mkdir(exist_ok=True)\ncam_gen  = SegGradCAM.attach(model)\n_data    = val_transforms(test_files[0])\n_inp     = _data[\"image\"].unsqueeze(0).to(device)\nsp_size  = tuple(_inp.shape[2:])\nsid      = test_files[0].get(\"subject_id\",\"unknown\")\n\nheatmaps = {}\nfor ci, cname in enumerate([\"TC\",\"WT\",\"ET\"]):\n    hm = cam_gen.generate(_inp, ci, sp_size)\n    heatmaps[cname] = hm\n    nib.save(nib.Nifti1Image(hm, np.eye(4)),\n             f\"{CFG.output_dir}/gradcam/{sid}_cam_{cname}.nii.gz\")\n    logger.info(f\"Saved CAM {cname}\")\ncam_gen